LABEL: G4 (Fuhrman)

LABEL: G4 (WHO)

LABEL: G4: Undifferentiated

definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of T2b, N0, and M0.

LABEL: Stage 3 (FIGO)

LABEL: Stage 3A (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of T3a, N0, and M0 .

LABEL: Stage 3B (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of T3b, N0, and M0 .

LABEL: Stage 3C (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of (T3c, N0,X and M0) or (any T, N1 and M0).

LABEL: Stage I (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers that are smaller or less deeply invasive without regional disease or nodes.

LABEL: Stage IA (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating invasive carcinoma which can be diagnosed only by microscopy, with deepest invasion <5 mm and the largest extension <7 mm.

LABEL: Stage IA1 (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating measured stromal invasion of <3.0 mm in depth and extension of <7.0 mm.

LABEL: Stage IA2 (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating measured stromal invasion of >3.0 mm and not >5.0 mm with an extension of not >7.0 mm.

LABEL: Stage IB (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating clinically visible lesions limited to the cervix uteri or pre-clinical cancers greater than stage IA

LABEL: Stage IB1 (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating clinically visible lesion limited to the cervix uteri or pre-clinical cancers greater than stage IA <4.0 cm in greatest dimension.

LABEL: Stage IB2 (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating clinically visible lesion limited to the cervix uteri or pre-clinical cancers greater than stage IA >4.0 cm in greatest dimension.

LABEL: Stage IIA (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers with increasing tumor or nodal extent but less than in Stage III and with differing characteristics from IIB and IIC.

LABEL: Stage IIA (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating cervical carcinoma invades beyond the uterus, but not to the pelvic wall or to the lower third of the vagina without parametrial invasion.

LABEL: Stage IIA1 (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating cervical carcinoma invades beyond the uterus, but not to the pelvic wall or to the lower third of the vagina without parametrial invasion and clinically visible lesion <4.0 cm in greatest dimension.

LABEL: Stage IIA2 (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating cervical carcinoma invades beyond the uterus, but not to the pelvic wall or to the lower third of the vagina without parametrial invasion and clinically visible lesion >4.0 cm in greatest dimension.

LABEL: Stage IIB (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers with increasing tumor or nodal extent but less than in Stage III and with differing characteristics from IIA and IIC.

LABEL: Stage IIB (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating cervical carcinoma invades beyond the uterus, but not to the pelvic wall or to the lower third of the vagina with obvious parametrial invasion.

LABEL: Stage IIC (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers with increasing tumor or nodal extent but less than in Stage III and with differing characteristics from IIA and IIB.

LABEL: Stage IIIA (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers with increasing tumor or nodal extent greater than in Stage II and with differing characteristics from IIIB and IIIC.

LABEL: Stage IIIA (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating tumour involves lower third of the vagina, with no extension to the pelvic wall.

LABEL: Stage IIIB (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers with increasing tumor or nodal extent greater than in Stage II and with differing characteristics from IIIA and IIIC.

LABEL: Stage IIIB (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating extension to the pelvic wall and/or hydronephrosis or non-functioning kidney.

LABEL: Stage IIIC (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers with increasing tumor or nodal extent greater than in Stage II and with differing characteristics from IIIA and IIIB.

LABEL: Stage IVA (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers in patients who present with distant metastases at diagnosis and with differing characteristics from IVB.

LABEL: Stage IVA (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating spread of the growth to adjacent organs.

LABEL: Stage IVB (AJCC 7th)
definition: A clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition indicating cancers in patients who present with distant metastases at diagnosis and with differing characteristics from IVA.

LABEL: Stage IVB (FIGO)
definition: An International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification indicating spread to distant organs.

LABEL: Stage Unknown (FIGO)
definition: A International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification associated with TNM stage values of (T0, N0, and M0) or (T1,1a-1c,2,2a-2c, NX, and M0) or (TX, N0,X, M0).

LABEL: Thermo Fisher Scientific
definition: An organization that is an American multinational, biotechnology product development company, created in 2006 by the merger of Thermo Electron and Fisher Scientific.

LABEL: Transformation-ML
definition: Transformation-ML is a format standard of a digital entity that is conformant with the Transformation-ML standard.(http://wiki.ficcs.org/ficcs/Transformation-ML?action=AttachFile&do=get&target=Transformation-ML_v1.0.26.pdf)

LABEL: XML
definition: XML is a format standard of a digital entity that is conformant with the W3C Extensible Markup Language Recommendation.(http://www.w3.org/XML/)

LABEL: accessInterface
definition: A software interface that 1) presents users with selection criteria and 2) presents products or services that meet the criteria the user then selects.

LABEL: action specification
definition: A directive information entity that describes an action the bearer will take.

LABEL: algorithm
definition: A plan specification which describes the inputs and output of mathematical functions as well as workflow of execution for achieving an predefined objective. Algorithms are realized usually by means of implementation as computer programs for execution by automata.

LABEL: anatomical cluster
definition: Anatomical group that has its parts adjacent to one another.

LABEL: angstrom
definition: A length unit which is equal to 10 [-10] m.

LABEL: assay
SubClass Of: capableOfDetecting some event|capableOfIdentifying some feature|createdBy some laboratoryProcedure
definition: An assay is an investigative (analytic) procedure for qualitatively assessing or quantitatively measuring the presence, amount, or functional activity of a target entity.

LABEL: author
definition: An originator or creator of a work

LABEL: cM0 (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there are no symptoms or signs of distant metastasis.

LABEL: cM0 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no distant metastasis.

LABEL: cM0 (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no distant metastasis.

LABEL: cM0 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no distant metastasis.

LABEL: cM1 (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is clinical evidence of distant metastases by history, physical examination, imaging studies, or invasive procedures, but without microscopic evidence of the presumed distant metastases.

LABEL: cM1 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there are distant metastases based on clinical assessment.

LABEL: cM1 (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there are distant metastases based on clinical assessment.

LABEL: cM1 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is distant metastasis except peritoneal metastasis based on clinical assessment.

LABEL: cM1a (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that metastasis is confined to one organ based on clinical assessment.

LABEL: cM1a (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that metastasis is based on clinical assessment and a separate tumor nodule(s) in a contralateral lobe; tumor with pleural nodules OR malignant pleural or pericardial effusion.

LABEL: cM1b (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that metastasis is in more than one organ or the peritoneum based on clinical assessment.

LABEL: cM1b (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is a distant metastases based on clinical assessment.

LABEL: campaign
definition: A systematic set of activities undertaken to meet a particular science objective.

LABEL: categorical label
definition: A label that is part of a categorical datum and that indicates the value of the data item on the categorical scale.

LABEL: categorical value specification
definition: A value specification that is specifies one category out of a fixed number of nominal categories

LABEL: centimeter
definition: A length unit which is equal to one hundredth of a meter or 10^[-2] m.

LABEL: class discovery data transformation
definition: A class discovery data transformation (sometimes called unsupervised classification) is a data transformation that has objective class discovery.
SYNONYMS: clustering data transformation|unsupervised classification data transformation

LABEL: class discovery objective
definition: A class discovery objective (sometimes called unsupervised classification) is a data transformation objective where the aim is to organize input data  (typically vectors of attributes) into classes, where the number of classes and their specifications are not known a priori. Depending on usage, the class assignment can be definite or probabilistic.
SYNONYMS: clustering objective|discriminant analysis objective|unsupervised classification objective

LABEL: class prediction data transformation
definition: A class prediction data transformation (sometimes called supervised classification) is a data transformation that has objective class prediction.

LABEL: class prediction objective
definition:
A class prediction objective (sometimes called supervised classification) is a data transformation objective where the aim is to create a predictor from training data through a machine learning technique. The training data consist of pairs of objects (typically vectors of attributes) and
class labels for these objects. The resulting predictor can be used to attach class labels to any valid novel input object. Depending on usage, the prediction can be definite or probabilistic. A classification is learned from the training data and can then be tested on test data.

LABEL: classified data set
SubClass Of: data set|is_specified_output_of some 'class prediction data transformation'
definition: A data set that is produced as the output of a class prediction data transformation and consists of a data set with assigned class labels.
SYNONYMS: data set with assigned class labels

LABEL: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of the stage of a cancer according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) v7 staging systems.

LABEL: clustered data set
SubClass Of: data set|is_specified_output_of some 'class discovery data transformation'
definition: A data set that is produced as the output of a class discovery data transformation and consists of a data set with assigned discovered class labels.
SYNONYMS: data set with assigned discovered class labels

LABEL: clustered data visualization
SubClass Of: data visualization|has_specified_input only 'clustered data set'|has_specified_output some ('dot plot' or histogram or heatmap or dendrogram or 'scatter plot')
definition: A data visualization which has input of a clustered data set and produces an output of a report graph which is capable of rendering data of this type.

LABEL: collection of specimens
definition: A material entity that has two or more specimens as its parts.

LABEL: colony forming unit per volume
definition: A concentration unit which a measure of viable bacterial numbers in a given volume.

LABEL: conclusion based on data
SubClass Of: information content entity|is_specified_output_of some 'drawing a conclusion based on data'|is_supported_by_data some 'data item'
definition: An information content entity that is inferred from data.

LABEL: continuant
definition: An entity that exists in full at any time in which it exists at all, persists through time while maintaining its identity and has no temporal parts.

LABEL: count per molar
definition: A rate unit which is equal to one over one molar.

LABEL: count per molar second
definition: A rate unit which is equal to one over one molar second.

LABEL: count per nanomolar
definition: A rate unit which is equal to one over one nanomolar.

LABEL: count per nanomolar second
definition: A rate unit which is equal to one over one nanomolar second.

LABEL: cross validation objective
definition: A cross validation objective is a data transformation objective in which the aim is to partition a sample of data into subsets such that the analysis is initially performed on a single subset, while the other subset(s) are retained for subsequent use in confirming and validating the initial analysis.

LABEL: cubic centimeter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a cubic meter or 10^[-9] m^[3], or to 1 ml.

LABEL: cubic decimeter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousand of a cubic meter or 10^[-3] m^[3], or to 1 L.

LABEL: curation status specification
definition: The curation status of the term. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

LABEL: data Product
SubClass Of: information content entity|is_specified_output_of some (mission or experiment)
definition: Processed data from the same source, normally compiled into a set according to shared characteristics.

LABEL: data about an ontology part
definition: Data about an ontology part is a data item about a part of an ontology, for example a term

LABEL: data element
definition: A data element is any characteristic that can help in understanding data content. That is, a data element is any parameter or variable that is useful, or critical, when identifying  or describing the content of a data object.

LABEL: data format specification
definition:
A data format specification is the information content borne by the document published defining the specification.
Example: The ISO document specifying what encompasses an XML document; The instructions in a XSD file

LABEL: data item
definition: An information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.

LABEL: data set
definition: A data item that is an aggregate of other data items of the same type that have something in common. Averages and distributions can be determined for data sets.

LABEL: data transformation
SubClass Of: achieves_planned_objective some 'data transformation objective'|has_specified_input only 'data item'|planned process|realizes some (concretizes some (algorithm and ('has part' some 'objective specification')))
definition: A planned process that produces output data from input data.

LABEL: data transformation objective
definition: An objective specification to transformation input data into output data

LABEL: data visualization
SubClass Of: has_specified_input only 'data item'|has_specified_input some 'data item'|has_specified_output only (graph or image)|has_specified_output some (graph or image)|planned process
definition: An planned process that creates images, diagrams or animations from the input data.

LABEL: dataset creating
definition: A planned process that has a data set as its specified output.

LABEL: datum label
definition: A label is a symbol that is part of some other datum and is used to either partially define  the denotation of that datum or to provide a means for identifying the datum as a member of the set of data with the same label

LABEL: day
definition: A time unit which is equal to 24 hours.

LABEL: decision tree building data transformation
SubClass Of: achieves_planned_objective some 'decision tree induction objective'|data transformation
definition: A decision tree building data transformation is a data transformation that has objective decision tree induction.

LABEL: decision tree induction objective
definition: A decision tree induction objective is a data transformation objective in which a tree-like graph of edges and nodes is created and from which the selection of each branch requires that some type of logical decision is made.

LABEL: defined class
definition: A defined class is a class that is defined by a set of logically necessary and sufficient conditions but is not a universal

LABEL: degree Celsius
definition: A temperature unit which is equal to one kelvin degree. However, they have their zeros at different points. The centigrade scale has its zero at 273.15 K.

LABEL: degree Fahrenheit
definition: A temperature unit which is equal to 5/9ths of a kelvin. Negative 40 degrees Fahrenheit is equal to negative 40 degrees Celsius.

LABEL: dendrogram
definition:
A dendrogram is a report graph which is a tree diagram
frequently used to illustrate the arrangement of the clusters produced by a
clustering algorithm.

LABEL: denotator type
definition: A denotator type indicates how a term should be interpreted from an ontological perspective.

LABEL: deployment
definition: The realisation of an application, or execution of a plan, idea, model, design, specification, standard, algorithm, or policy.

LABEL: device
definition: A material entity that is designed to perform a function in a scientific investigation, but is not a reagent.

LABEL: diagram
definition: A figure that expresses one or more propositions

LABEL: dimensionality reduction
SubClass Of: (has_specified_output some 'clustered data set') and (achieves_planned_objective some 'class discovery objective')|class discovery data transformation|dataset creating
definition: A dimensionality reduction is data partitioning which transforms each input m-dimensional vector (x_1, x_2, ..., x_m) into an output n-dimensional vector (y_1, y_2, ..., y_n), where n is smaller than m.

LABEL: directive information entity
definition: An information content entity whose concretizations indicate to their bearer how to realize them in a process.

LABEL: discoveryInterface
SubClass Of: aggregate some applicationDiscoveryCriterion|aggregate some dataDiscoveryCriterion|aggregate some informationDiscoveryCriterion|aggregate some modelDiscoveryCriterion|aggregate some toolDiscoveryCriterion|leadTo some accessInterface|present some discoveryCriterion
definition: An interface that allows the user to discover the existence of relevant products and services.

LABEL: document
definition: A written or printed paper that bears the original, official, or legal form of something and can be used to furnish decisive evidence or information.

LABEL: document
definition: A collection of information content entities intended to be understood together as a whole

LABEL: documenting
SubClass Of: has_specified_input some 'information content entity'|has_specified_output some document|planned process
definition: A planned process in which a document is created or added to by including the specified input in it.

LABEL: dot plot
definition: A dot plot is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data where each data point is represented by a single dot placed on coordinates corresponding to data point values in particular dimensions.

LABEL: drawing a conclusion based on data
SubClass Of: has_specified_input some 'data item'|has_specified_output some 'conclusion based on data'|planned process
definition: A planned process in which data gathered in an investigation is evaluated in the context of existing knowledge with the objective to generate more general conclusions or to conclude that the data does not allow one to draw general conclusion

LABEL: eBioscience
definition: A supplier of flow cytometry analyzers

LABEL: event
definition: Something observable that happened at a given time and place

LABEL: experiment
SubClass Of: componentOf some researchInvestigation|conductedAt some facility|conductedOn some organism|generates some specimen|partOf some mission|planned process|uses some 'experiment Apparatus'
definition: A plan for a coordinated set of actions and observations designed to generate data, with the ultimate goal of discovery or hypothesis testing.

LABEL: experiment
SubClass Of: 'has participant' some biospecimen|'has participant' some institution|'has participant' some investigator|'has participant' some payload|'has participant' some personnel|'has participant' some subject|experiment|fundedBy some program|generates some dataset|investigation|managedAt some nasa_center|uses some hardware

LABEL: experiment Apparatus
definition: Hardware used in conducting an experiment.

LABEL: factor
definition: The role played by an entity as part of a scientific investigation such that levels of the measurement or observation of the entity are thought to bear upon the hypotheses being investigated.

LABEL: failed exploratory term
definition: The term was used in an attempt to structure part of the ontology but in retrospect failed to do a good job

LABEL: feature
SubClass Of: characterizedBy some (experiment or observation)|material entity|quantifiedBy some (experiment or observation)
definition: A material entity that has characteristics that can be qualified or quantified through observation or experiment.

LABEL: figure
definition: An information content entity consisting of a two dimensional arrangement of information content entities such that the arrangement itself is about something.

LABEL: firmware
definition: Software that provides the low-level control for a device's specific hardware.

LABEL: funder
definition: A role in which the bearer delivers financial support to enable some activity.

LABEL: generically dependent continuant
definition: A continuant that is dependent on one or other independent continuant bearers. For every instance of A requires some instance of (an independent continuant type) B but which instance of B serves can change from time to time.|b is a generically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant that g-depends_on one or more other entities. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [074-001])

LABEL: gram
definition: A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of a kilogram or 10^[-3] kg.

LABEL: gram per deciliter
definition: A mass density unit which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in deciliters.

LABEL: gram per liter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in liters.

LABEL: graph
definition: A diagram that presents one or more tuples of information by mapping those tuples in to a two dimensional space in a non arbitrary way.

LABEL: hardware
definition: The mechanical, magnetic, electronic, and electrical equipment necessary for conducting an activity.

LABEL: heatmap
definition:
A heatmap is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data
where the values taken by a variable(s) are shown as colors in a
two-dimensional map.

LABEL: hertz
definition: A frequency unit which is equal to 1 complete cycle of a recurring phenomenon in 1 second.

LABEL: hierarchical clustering
SubClass Of: (has_specified_output some 'clustered data set') and (achieves_planned_objective some 'class discovery objective')|class discovery data transformation|dataset creating
definition: A hierarchical clustering is a data transformation which achieves a class discovery objective, which takes as input data item and builds a hierarchy of clusters. The traditional representation of this hierarchy is a tree (visualized by a dendrogram), with the individual input objects at one end (leaves) and a single cluster containing every object at the other (root).

LABEL: histogram
definition:
A histogram is a report graph which is a statistical description of a
distribution in terms of occurrence frequencies of different event classes.

LABEL: histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a tumor slide specimen according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) 7th Edition grading system.

LABEL: histologic grade according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System
definition: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a tumor slide specimen according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System.

LABEL: histologic grade for ovarian tumor
definition: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a ovarian tumor.

LABEL: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to a two-tier grading system
definition: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor that is from a two-tier histological classification of tumors.

LABEL: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to the World Health Organization
definition: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor that is from a histological classification by the World Health Organization (WHO).

LABEL: hour
definition: A time unit which is equal to 3600 seconds or 60 minutes.

LABEL: image
definition: An image is an affine projection to a two dimensional surface, of measurements of some quality of an entity or entities repeated at regular intervals across a spatial range, where the measurements are represented as color and luminosity on the projected on surface.

LABEL: independent continuant
definition: A continuant that is a bearer of quality and realizable entity entities, in which other entities inhere and which itself cannot inhere in anything.|b is an independent continuant = Def. b is a continuant which is such that there is no c and no t such that b s-depends_on c at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [017-002])

LABEL: information content entity
definition: A generically dependent continuant that is about some thing.

LABEL: instrument
definition: An instrument is a physical object that can be used to collect data.

LABEL: investigation
SubClass Of: 'has part' some 'drawing a conclusion based on data'|'has part' some 'study design execution'|'has part' some (planning and (has_specified_output some 'study design'))|'has part' some documenting|planned process
definition: a planned process that consists of parts: planning, study design execution, documentation and which produce conclusion(s).

LABEL: investigation agent role
SubClass Of: 'inheres in' some ('bearer of' some (concretizes some (objective_achieved_by some ('part of' some investigation))))|'realized in' only investigation|role
definition: A role borne by an entity and that is realized in a process that is part of an investigation in which an objective is achieved. These processes include, among others: planning, overseeing, funding, reviewing.

LABEL: k-means clustering
SubClass Of: (has_specified_output some 'clustered data set') and (achieves_planned_objective some 'class discovery objective')|class discovery data transformation|dataset creating|partitioning data transformation
definition: A k-means clustering is a data transformation which achieves a class discovery or partitioning objective, which takes as input a collection of objects (represented as points in multidimensional space) and which partitions them into a specified number k of clusters. The algorithm attempts to find the centers of natural clusters in the data. The most common form of the algorithm starts by partitioning the input points into k initial sets, either at random or using some heuristic data. It then calculates the mean point, or centroid, of each set. It constructs a new partition by associating each point with the closest centroid. Then the centroids are recalculated for the new clusters, and the algorithm repeated by alternate applications of these two steps until convergence, which is obtained when the points no longer switch clusters (or alternatively centroids are no longer changed).

LABEL: k-nearest neighbors
SubClass Of: (has_specified_output some 'clustered data set') and (achieves_planned_objective some 'class discovery objective')|class discovery data transformation|dataset creating|partitioning data transformation
definition: A k-nearest neighbors is a data transformation which achieves a class discovery or partitioning objective, in which an input data object with vector y is assigned to a class label based upon the k closest training data set points to y; where k is the largest value that class label is assigned.

LABEL: kilogram
definition: A mass unit which is equal to the mass of the International Prototype Kilogram kept by the BIPM at Svres, France.

LABEL: laboratoryProcedure
definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample or subject in a laboratory setting

LABEL: leave one out cross validation method
definition: is a data transformation :  leave-one-out cross-validation (LOOCV) involves using a single observation from the original sample as the validation data, and the remaining observations as the training data. This is repeated such that each observation in the sample is used once as the validation data

LABEL: length unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the distance between two points.

LABEL: liter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of a cubic meter or 10^[-3] m^[3], or to 1 decimeter.

LABEL: manufacturer
definition: A person or organization that has a manufacturer role

LABEL: manufacturer role
SubClass Of: 'inheres in' some ('Homo sapiens' or organization)|'realized in' only manufacturing|role
definition: Manufacturer role is a role which inheres in a person or organization and which is realized by a manufacturing process.

LABEL: manufacturing
SubClass Of: achieves_planned_objective some 'manufacturing objective'|has_specified_input some 'material entity'|material processing
definition: Manufacturing is a process with the intent to produce a processed material which will have a function for future use. A person or organization (having manufacturer role) is a participant in this process

LABEL: manufacturing objective
definition: is the objective to manufacture a material of a certain function (device)

LABEL: mass percentage
definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the mass of a substance in a mixture as a percentage of the mass of the entire mixture.

LABEL: mass unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of matter/energy of a physical object.

LABEL: mass volume percentage
definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the mass of the substance in a mixture as a percentage of the volume of the entire mixture.

LABEL: material anatomical entity
definition: Anatomical entity that has mass.

LABEL: material entity
definition: An independent continuant that is spatially extended whose identity is independent of that of other entities and can be maintained through time.

LABEL: material information bearer
SubClass Of: 'bearer of' some (concretizes some 'information content entity')|material entity
definition: A material entity in which a concretization of an information content entity inheres.

LABEL: material processing
SubClass Of: achieves_planned_objective some 'material transformation objective'|has_specified_input only 'material entity'|has_specified_output some 'processed material'|planned process
definition: A planned process which results in physical changes in a specified input material

LABEL: material supplier
definition: A person or organization that provides material supplies to other people or organizations.

LABEL: material supplier role
definition: a role realized through the process of supplying materials such as animal subjects, reagents or other materials used in an investigation.

LABEL: material transformation objective
definition: an objective specifiction that creates an specific output object from input materials.

LABEL: measurement unit label
definition: A measurement unit label is as a label that is part of a scalar measurement datum and denotes a unit of measure.

LABEL: metadata complete
definition: Class has all its metadata, but is either not guaranteed to be in its final location in the asserted IS_A hierarchy or refers to another class that is not complete.

LABEL: metadata incomplete
definition: Class is being worked on; however, the metadata (including definition) are not complete or sufficiently clear to the branch editors.

LABEL: meter
definition: A length unit which is equal to the length of the path traveled by light in vacuum during a time interval of 1/299 792 458 of a second.

LABEL: microgram
definition: A mass unit which is equal to one millionth of a gram or 10^[-6] g.

LABEL: microgram per liter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in micrograms divided by the volume in liters.

LABEL: microliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a liter or 10^[-6] L.

LABEL: microliters per minute
definition: A volumetric flow rate unit which is equal to one microliter volume through a given surface in one minute.

LABEL: micrometer
definition: A length unit which is equal to one millionth of a meter or 10^[-6] m.

LABEL: micromolar
definition: A unit of molarity which is equal to one millionth of a molar or 10^[-6] M.

LABEL: micromole
definition: A substance unit equal to a millionth of a mol or 10^[-6] mol.

LABEL: milligram
definition: A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of a gram or 10^[-3] g.

LABEL: milligram per milliliter
definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in milligrams divided by the volume in milliliters.

LABEL: milliliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of a liter or 10^[-3] L, or to 1 cubic centimeter.

LABEL: milliliter per liter
definition: A volume per unit volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a liter of solute in one liter of solution.

LABEL: millimeter
definition: A length unit which is equal to one thousandth of a meter or 10^[-3] m.

LABEL: millimolar
definition: A unit of molarity which is equal to one thousandth of a molar or 10^[-3] M.

LABEL: minute
definition: A time unit which is equal to 60 seconds.

LABEL: mission
SubClass Of: deployedOn some hardware|organizedBy some spaceAgency|planned process
definition: A mission is a named activity for some purpose

LABEL: molar
definition: A unit of concentration which expresses a concentration of 1 mole of solute per liter of solution (mol/L).

LABEL: month
definition: A time unit which is approximately equal to the length of time of one of cycle of the moon's phases which in science is taken to be equal to 30 days.

LABEL: named class expression
definition: A named class expression is a logical expression that is given a name. The name can be used in place of the expression.

LABEL: nanogram
definition: A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a gram or 10^[-9] g.

LABEL: nanoliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a liter or 10^[-9] L.

LABEL: nanometer
definition: A length unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a meter or 10^[-9] m.

LABEL: nanomolar
definition: A unit of molarity which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a molar or 10^[-9] M.

LABEL: nanomole
definition: A substance unit equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a mole or 10^[-9] mol.

LABEL: objective specification
definition: A directive information entity that describes an intended process endpoint. When part of a plan specification the concretization is realized in a planned process in which the bearer tries to effect the world so that the process endpoint is achieved.

LABEL: obsolescence reason specification
definition: The reason for which a term has been deprecated. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

LABEL: occurrent
definition: An entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds or develops through time.

LABEL: organism
definition: The quality of a living subject that indicates the taxonomical grouping of the subject.  This grouping can be at any level in a hierachy of organism classification, or a collection of levels, and can be using scientific language or colloquial language.

LABEL: organism
definition: A material entity that is an individual living system, such as animal, plant, bacteria or virus, that is capable of replicating or reproducing, growth and maintenance in the right environment. An organism may be unicellular or made up, like humans, of many billions of cells divided into specialized tissues and organs.

LABEL: organization
SubClass Of: hasRole some author|hasRole some funder|hasRole some investigator|hasRole some spaceAgency

LABEL: organization
definition: An entity that can bear roles, has members, and has a set of organization rules. Members of organizations are either organizations themselves or individual people. Members can bear specific organization member roles that are determined in the organization rules. The organization rules also determine how decisions are made on behalf of the organization by the organization members.

LABEL: organizational term
definition: Term created to ease viewing/sort terms for development purpose, and will not be included in a release

LABEL: pH
definition: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the acidity of a solution in terms of activity of hydrogen ions (H+).

LABEL: pM1 (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is microscopic evidence confirming distant metastatic disease.

LABEL: pM1 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is a distant metastases that is histologically confirmed.

LABEL: pM1 (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is a distant metastases that is histologically confirmed.

LABEL: pM1 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is distant metastasis except peritoneal metastasis that is histologically confirmed.

LABEL: pM1a (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that metastasis is confined to one organ and histologically confirmed.

LABEL: pM1a (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that metastasis is histologically confirmed and a separate tumor nodule(s) in a contralateral lobe; tumor with pleural nodules OR malignant pleural or pericardial effusion.

LABEL: pM1b (colon)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that metastasis is in more than one organ or the peritoneum and histologically confirmed.

LABEL: pM1b (lung)
definition: A pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is a distant metastases that is histologically confirmed and associated with distant lymph nodes or carcinomatosis.

LABEL: pN0 (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating no regional lymph node metastsis.

LABEL: pN0 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no regional lymph node metastasis.

LABEL: pN0 (lung)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating no regional lymph node metastasis.

LABEL: pN0 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no regional lymph node metastasis.

LABEL: pN1 (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in 1-3 regional lymph nodes.

LABEL: pN1 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is regional lymph node metastasis.

LABEL: pN1 (lung)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in ipsilateral peribronchial and/or ipsilateral hilar lymph nodes and intrapulmonary nodes, including involvement by direct extension.

LABEL: pN1 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is regional lymph node metastasis.

LABEL: pN1a (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in 1 regional lymph node.

LABEL: pN1b (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in 2-3 regional lymph nodes.

LABEL: pN1c (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating tumor deposit(s), i.e., satellites in the subserosa, or in non-peritonealized pericolic or perirectal soft tissue without regional lymph node metastasis.

LABEL: pN2 (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in 4 or more regional lymph nodes.

LABEL: pN2 (lung)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in ipsilateral mediastinal and/or subcarinal lymph node(s).

LABEL: pN2a (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in 4 to 6 regional lymph nodes.

LABEL: pN2b (colon)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in 7 or more regional lymph nodes.

LABEL: pN3 (lung)
definition: A pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating metastasis in contralateral mediastinal, contralateral hilar, ipsilateral or contralateral scalene, or supraclavicular lymph node(s).

LABEL: pT0 (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no evidence of primary tumor.

LABEL: pT0 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no evidence of primary tumor.

LABEL: pT0 (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no evidence of primary tumor.

LABEL: pT0 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that there is no evidence of primary tumor.

LABEL: pT1 (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor invades submucosa.

LABEL: pT1 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is 7 cm or less in greatest dimension and limited to the kidney.

LABEL: pT1 (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is 3 cm or less in greatest dimension, surrounded by lung or visceral pleura without bronchoscopic evidence of invasion more proximal than the lobar bronchus (i.e., not in the main bronchus).

LABEL: pT1 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is limited to the ovaries (one or both).

LABEL: pT1a (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is 4 cm or less.

LABEL: pT1a (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is 2 cm or less in greatest dimension.

LABEL: pT1a (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is limited to one ovary; capsule intact, no tumor on ovarian surface and no malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings.

LABEL: pT1b (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 4 cm but not more than 7 cm.

LABEL: pT1b (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 2 cm but not more than 3 cm in greatest dimension.

LABEL: pT1b (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is limited to both ovaries; capsule intact, no tumor on ovarian surface and no malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings.

LABEL: pT1c (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is limited to one or both ovaries with capsule ruptured, tumor on ovarian surface, or malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings.

LABEL: pT2 (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor invades muscularis propria.

LABEL: pT2 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 7 cm in greatest dimension and limited to the kidney.

LABEL: pT2 (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 3 cm but not more than 7 cm or the tumor has any of the following features: involves main bronchus, 2 cm or more distal to the carina, invades visceral pleura, associated with atelectasis or obstructive pneumonitis that extends to the hilar region but does not involve the entire lung.

LABEL: pT2 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor involves one or both ovaries with pelvic extension.

LABEL: pT2a (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 7 cm but not more than 10 cm.

LABEL: pT2a (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 3 cm but not more than 5 cm in greatest dimension.

LABEL: pT2a (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor has extension and/or implants on uterus and/or tube(s) and no malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings.

LABEL: pT2b (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 10 cm and limited to the kidney.

LABEL: pT2b (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 5 cm but not more than 7 cm in greatest dimension.

LABEL: pT2b (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor has extension to other pelvic tissues and no malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings.

LABEL: pT2c (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor has pelvic extension with malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings.

LABEL: pT3 (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor invades subserosa or into non-peritionealized pericolic or perirectal tissues.

LABEL: pT3 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor extends into major veins or perinephric tissues but not into the ipsilateral adrenal gland and not beyond the Gerota fascia.

LABEL: pT3 (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor is more than 7 cm or one that directly invades any of: parietal pleura, chest wall (including superior sulcus tumors), diaphragm, phrenic nerve, mediastinal pleura, parietal pericardiu or the tumor is in the main bronchus less than 2 cm distal to the carina but without  involvement of the carina or there is associated atelectasis or obstructive pneumonitis of the entire lung or there is separate tumor nodule(s) in the same lobe as the primary.

LABEL: pT3 (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor involves one or both ovaries with microscopically confirmed peritoneal metastasis outside the pelvis and/or regional lymph node metastasis.

LABEL: pT3a (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor grossly extends into the renal vein or its segmental (muscle containing) branches, or the tumor invades perirenal and/or renal sinus fat (peripelvic) fat but not beyond Gerota fascia.

LABEL: pT3a (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor has microscopic peritoneal metastasis beyond pelvis.

LABEL: pT3b (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor grossly extends into vena cava below diaphragm.

LABEL: pT3b (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor has macroscopic peritoneal, metastatasis beyond pelvis, 2 cm or less in greatest dimension.

LABEL: pT3c (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor grossly extends into vena cava above the diaphragm or Invades the wall of the vena cava.

LABEL: pT3c (ovary)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor has peritoneal metastasis beyond pelvis, more than 2 cm in greatest dimension and/or regional lymph node metastasis.

LABEL: pT4 (kidney)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor invades beyond Gerota fascia (including contiguous extension into the ipsilateral adrenal gland).

LABEL: pT4 (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor of any size that invades any of the following: mediastinum, heart, great vessels, trachea, recurrent laryngeal nerve, esophagus, vertebral body, carina or there is separate tumor nodule(s) in a different ipsilateral lobe to that of the primary.

LABEL: pT4a (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor perforates visceral peritoneum.

LABEL: pT4b (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating that the tumor directly invades other organs or structures.

LABEL: pTis (colon)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition indicating carcinoma in situ (intraepithelial or invasion of lamina propria).

LABEL: pTis (lung)
definition: A pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition indicating carcinoma in situ.

LABEL: partitioning data transformation
definition: A partitioning data transformation is a data transformation that has objective partitioning.

LABEL: partitioning objective
definition: A partitioning objective is a data transformation objective where the aim is to generate a collection of disjoint non-empty subsets whose union equals a non-empty input set.

LABEL: pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of colon cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

LABEL: pathologic distant metastases stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

LABEL: pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

LABEL: pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a  pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

LABEL: pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of colorectal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.
SYNONYMS: pN: Pathologic spread colon lymph nodes (AJCC 7th Edition)

LABEL: pathologic lymph node stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.
SYNONYMS: pN: Pathologic spread kidney lymph nodes (AJCC 7th Edition)

LABEL: pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

SYNONYMS: pN: Pathologic spread colon lymph nodes (AJCC 7th Edition)

LABEL: pathologic lymph node stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.
SYNONYMS: pN: Pathologic spread ovarian lymph nodes (AJCC 7th Edition)

LABEL: pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition

TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.
SYNONYMS: pT: Pathologic spread colorectal primary tumor (AJCC 7th Edition)

LABEL: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition
definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.
SYNONYMS: pT: Pathologic spread kidney primary tumor (AJCC 7th Edition)

definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer following the rules of the TNM American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) version 7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.
SYNONYMS: pT: Pathologic spread lung primary tumor (AJCC 7th Edition)

TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

LABEL: pds_Data_Set_PDS3
definition: A data Product from the PDS system.

LABEL: peak matching
definition: Peak matching is a data transformation performed on a dataset of a graph of ordered data points (e.g. a spectrum) with the objective of pattern matching local maxima above a noise threshold

LABEL: pending final vetting
definition: All definitions, placement in the asserted IS_A hierarchy and required minimal metadata are complete. The class is awaiting a final review by someone other than the term editor.

LABEL: performance status value specification
definition: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of a participant's performance status (general well-being and activities of daily life).

LABEL: personnel
SubClass Of: 'member of' some institution|'member of' some nasa_center|Homo sapiens|operates some payload|person

LABEL: picogram
definition: A mass unit which is equal to 10^[-12] g.

LABEL: picoliter
definition: A volume unit which is equal to 10^[-12] L.

LABEL: picomolar
definition: A unit of molarity which is equal to 10^[-12] M.

LABEL: picomole
definition: A substance unit equal to 10^[-12] mol.

LABEL: plan specification
SubClass Of: 'has part' some 'action specification'|'has part' some 'objective specification'|directive information entity
definition: A directive information entity with action specifications and objective specifications as parts that, when concretized, is realized in a process in which the bearer tries to achieve the objectives by taking the actions specified.

LABEL: planned process
definition: A process that realizes a plan which is the concretization of a plan specification.

LABEL: planning
definition: a process of creating or modifying a plan specification

LABEL: platform
definition: A platform in the context of NASA's SMD catalog

LABEL: principal components analysis dimensionality reduction
definition: A principal components analysis dimensionality reduction is a dimensionality reduction achieved by applying principal components analysis and by keeping low-order principal components and excluding higher-order ones.

LABEL: process
definition: An occurrent that has temporal proper parts and for some time t, p s-depends_on some material entity at t.|p is a process = Def. p is an occurrent that has temporal proper parts and for some time t, p s-depends_on some material entity at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [083-003])

LABEL: processed material
definition: Is a material entity that is created or changed during material processing.

LABEL: processed specimen
definition: A specimen that has been intentionally physically modified.

LABEL: protocol
definition: A plan specification which has sufficient level of detail and quantitative information to communicate it between investigation agents, so that different investigation agents will reliably be able to independently reproduce the process.

LABEL: questionnaire
definition: A document with a set of printed or written questions with a choice of answers, devised for the purposes of a survey or statistical study.

LABEL: ready for release
definition: Class has undergone final review, is ready for use, and will be included in the next release. Any class lacking "ready_for_release" should be considered likely to change place in hierarchy, have its definition refined, or be obsoleted in the next release.  Those classes deemed "ready_for_release" will also derived from a chain of ancestor classes that are also "ready_for_release."

LABEL: realizable entity
definition: A specifically dependent continuant  that inheres in continuant  entities and are not exhibited in full at every time in which it inheres in an entity or group of entities. The exhibition or actualization of a realizable entity is a particular manifestation, functioning or process that occurs under certain circumstances.

LABEL: regulator role
definition: a regulatory role involved with making and/or enforcing relevant legislation and governmental orders

LABEL: regulatory agency
definition: A regulatory agency is a organization that has responsibility over or for  the legislation (acts and regulations) for a given sector of the government.

LABEL: regulatory role
definition: a role which inheres in material entities and is realized in the processes of making, enforcing or being defined by legislation or orders issued by a governmental body.

LABEL: requires discussion
definition: A term that is metadata complete, has been reviewed, and problems have been identified that require discussion before release. Such a term requires editor note(s) to identify the outstanding issues.

LABEL: researchMission
SubClass Of: 'part of' some program|implements some experiment|implements some researchInvestigation|investigates some research_area|mission|obo:SDDO_3000112|planned process|uses some payload

LABEL: role
definition: A realizable entity  the manifestation of which brings about some result or end that is not essential to a continuant  in virtue of the kind of thing that it is but that can be served or participated in by that kind of continuant  in some kinds of natural, social or institutional contexts.

LABEL: scatter plot
definition: A scatterplot is a graph which uses Cartesian coordinates to display values for two variables for a set of data. The data is displayed as a collection of points, each having the value of one variable determining the position on the horizontal axis and the value of the other variable determining the position on the vertical axis.

LABEL: second
definition: A time unit which is equal to the duration of 9 192 631 770 periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the ground state of the caesium 133 atom.

LABEL: service provider role
SubClass Of: 'inheres in' some ('Homo sapiens' or organization)|'realized in' only 'planned process'|role
definition: is a role which inheres in a person or organization and is realized in in a planned process which provides access to training, materials or execution of protocols for an organization or person

LABEL: software
definition:
Software is a plan specification composed of a series of instructions that can be 
interpreted by or directly executed by a processing unit.

LABEL: software development
SubClass Of: has_specified_output some (software or 'source code module')|planned process
definition: A planned process that has specified output a software product and that involves the creation of source code.

LABEL: source code module
definition: A source code module is a directive information entity that specifies, using a programming language, some algorithm.

LABEL: spase:Catalog
definition: A tabular listing of events or observational notes, especially those that have utility in aiding a user in locating data.

LABEL: spase:DisplayData
definition: A graphical representation of data wherein the underlying numeric values are not (readily) accessible for analysis.

LABEL: spase:NumericalData
definition: Data stored as numerical values in one or more specified formats.

LABEL: specifically dependent continuant
definition: A continuant that inheres in or is borne by other entities. Every instance of A requires some specific instance of B which must always be the same.|b is a relational specifically dependent continuant = Def. b is a specifically dependent continuant and there are n > 1 independent continuants c1,  cn which are not spatial regions are such that for all 1  i < j  n, ci  and cj share no common parts, are such that for each 1  i  n, b s-depends_on ci at every time t during the course of bs existence (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [131-004])|b is a specifically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant & there is some independent continuant c which is not a spatial region and which is such that b s-depends_on c at every time t during the course of bs existence. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [050-003])

LABEL: specimen
definition: A part of a feature, taken to demonstrate or to determine the character of the whole.

LABEL: specimen
definition: A material entity that has the specimen role.

LABEL: specimen collection objective
definition: A objective specification to obtain a material entity for potential use as an input during an investigation.

LABEL: specimen collection process
SubClass Of: achieves_planned_objective some 'specimen collection objective'|has_specified_input some 'material entity'|has_specified_output some specimen|planned process
definition: A planned process with the objective of collecting a specimen.

LABEL: specimen from organism
SubClass Of: 'derives from' some ('material anatomical entity' or 'anatomical cluster')|specimen
definition: A specimen that derives from an anatomical part or substance arising from an organism. Examples of tissue specimen include tissue, organ, physiological system, blood, or body location (arm).

LABEL: specimen role
SubClass Of: 'inheres in' some ('material entity' and (is_specified_output_of some 'specimen collection process'))|role
definition: a role borne by a material entity that is gained during a specimen collection process and that can be realized by use of the specimen in an investigation

LABEL: statistical model validation
SubClass Of: achieves_planned_objective some 'cross validation objective'|partitioning data transformation
definition: A data transformation which assesses how the results of a statistical analysis will generalize to an independent data set.

LABEL: study
definition: A data product from the GeneLab repository

LABEL: study design
definition: A plan specification comprised of protocols (which may specify how and what kinds of data will be gathered) that are executed as part of an investigation and is realized during a study design execution.

LABEL: study design execution
definition: a planned process that carries out a study design

LABEL: support vector machine
SubClass Of: achieves_planned_objective some 'class prediction objective'|class prediction data transformation
definition: A support vector machine is a data transformation with a class prediction objective based on the construction of a separating hyperplane that maximizes the margin between two data sets of vectors in n-dimensional space.

LABEL: tar
definition: tar is a format standard of a digital entity that is conformant with the tape archive file format as standardized by POSIX.1-1998, POSIX.1-2001, or any other tar format compliant with the GNU tar specification. (http://www.gnu.org/software/tar/manual/)

LABEL: time unit
definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the dimension in which events occur in sequence.

LABEL: to be replaced with external ontology term
definition: Terms with this status should eventually replaced with a term from another ontology.

LABEL: uncurated
definition: Nothing done yet beyond assigning a unique class ID and proposing a preferred term.

LABEL: value specification
definition: An information content entity that specifies a value within a classification scheme or on a quantitative scale.

LABEL: volume percentage
definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the volume of the solute in mL per 100 mL of the resulting solution.

LABEL: week
definition: A time unit which is equal to 7 days.

LABEL: year
definition: A time unit which is equal to 12 months which is science is taken to be equal to 365.25 days.

LABEL: zip
definition: zip is a format standard of a digital entity that is conformant with the PKWARE .ZIP file format specification  (http://www.pkware.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=59&Itemid=103/)
